==English==
===Etymology===
Arabic {{ARchar|القائد البنات النعش}} (''al-qā’id al-banāt an-na‘sh'') ‘the leader of the girls at the bier’, from {{ARchar|[[قائد]]}} ‘leader’ + {{ARchar|[[بنات]]}} plural of {{ARchar|[[بنت]]}} ‘girl’ + {{ARchar|[[نعش]]}} ‘bier’.  With reference to the mourners at the funeral of [[Calypso]] (who became the [[Great Bear]]).

===Noun===
'''Alkaid'''
# a [[star]] in the [[constellation]] of [[Ursa Major]], the east-most star of the [[Plough]]

===Synonyms===
*[[Eta Ursae Majoris]]
*[[Benetnash]]

